      "parameters": {
        "content": "# 📝 Webhook → Notion Logger\n\nReceives any webhook event and logs it as a\nstructured row in a Notion database — perfect\nfor tracking form submissions, API calls, or events\nfrom any external service.\n\nAuthor: Slim Khardani\nGitHub: github.com/slimkhardani",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 528,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -480,
        -352
      ],
      "id": "f1900009-06de-412e-b111-8afd27eaf1e4",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⚙️ Setup Required\n\n1. Notion Integration Token\n   → notion.so/my-integrations\n   → Create integration → copy token\n\n2. Connect integration to your database\n   → Open your Notion database\n   → ••• → Connections → Add your integration\n\n3. Database must have these properties:\n   Source (Text), Event Type (Text),\n   Payload (Text), Received At (Date)",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -480,
